## API Versioning

### URL prefix versioning (recommended)
```ts
// app.ts
import v1Router from './routes/v1';
import v2Router from './routes/v2';

app.use('/api/v1', v1Router);
app.use('/api/v2', v2Router);

// Latest alias
app.use('/api', v2Router);
```

### Deprecation headers
```ts
// Middleware for deprecated routes
export function deprecated(sunsetDate: string): RequestHandler {
  return (req, res, next) => {
    res.setHeader('Deprecation', 'true');
    res.setHeader('Sunset', sunsetDate); // RFC 8594
    res.setHeader('Link', '</api/v2/users>; rel="successor-version"');
    next();
  };
}

// Usage
v1Router.get('/users', deprecated('2025-01-01'), listUsersV1);
```

**Rules:**
- Never break a route without a deprecation period (minimum 6 months)
- Log usage of deprecated endpoints to track client migration
- Document breaking changes in a CHANGELOG
- Consider header-based versioning (`API-Version: 2`) for internal APIs
